commit d35425f42fb834da33ccc851cb91dc83d7daf018
Author: Konstantin <rsboarder@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 2 20:02:42 2026 +0400

    fix: point cursor seat at cursor-agent binary, not PATH-hijacked agent (#2)
    
    The cursor runner invoked the bare binary name `agent`. During Grok seat
    testing, the Grok CLI installed ~/.grok/bin/agent earlier on PATH, so
    shutil.which("agent") and the subprocess both resolved to Grok, not Cursor.
    Every council since May 28 silently lost the cursor seat — and claudeor,
    which fell back onto the same binary — with:
    
        error: a value is required for '--single <PROMPT>' but none was supplied
    
    (`--single` is Grok's headless flag; Cursor uses `--print`.)
    
    Point all three references at the unambiguous `cursor-agent` binary:
    the cli_command availability check, both exec/resume argv, and the
    dashboard CLI-version probe.
    
    Co-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

